    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Describe your issue\n\nHi,\nI’ve been using Cython recently and spent some time browsing the documentation. I noticed the docs are still using an older Sphinx theme, which is, of course, completely fine and functional.\n\nI have created a new [Clarity theme for Sphinx](https://github.com/ReadCraft-io/sphinx-clarity-theme) recently. Out of curiosity, I made a small fork where I tried rendering the same documentation with the Clarity theme, just as a side experiment.\n\nI’m not suggesting any change, but I thought I’d share the preview in case you find it interesting or useful.\n\n– new docs: https://showcase.readcraft.io/cython/ (announcement bar with \"see stable\" does not work in this demo)\n– fork: https://github.com/ReadCraft-io/showcase-cython\n\nI could send a PR. Or if this isn’t something you want to consider, feel free to ignore it — I just wanted to share the experiment.\n\nThanks for creating Cython 🙏",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
